---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import TrustSignal from '../components/TrustSignal.astro';
---

<BaseLayout
  title="feedbackmonk"
  description="Privacy-first product feedback. AGPL-licensed widget + admin + roadmap. Self-host or SaaS. Zero third-party trackers."
>
  <section class="hero">
    <p class="eyebrow">AGPL-3.0 · privacy-first · self-host or SaaS</p>
    <h1>Product feedback that respects your users.</h1>
    <p class="lede">
      feedbackmonk is an open-source feedback platform &mdash; submission widget,
      triage queue, public roadmap with voting, status emails. No third-party
      trackers; the only identity we hold is the JWT your app signs.
    </p>

    <div class="hero-cta">
      <a class="btn-primary" href="/pricing">See pricing</a>
      <a class="btn-secondary" href="/docs/self-host">Self-host docs</a>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section aria-labelledby="trust-signals-heading" class="trust-section">
    <h2 id="trust-signals-heading" class="trust-heading">What we promise</h2>
    <ul class="trust-list">
      <TrustSignal
        title="EU + US hosting"
        evidence="region selectable per tenant"
      />
      <TrustSignal
        title="Open-source core (AGPL-3.0)"
        evidence="github.com/feedbackmonk/feedbackmonk"
        href="https://github.com/feedbackmonk/feedbackmonk"
      />
      <TrustSignal
        title="Zero third-party trackers"
        evidence="verified in CI (widget-bundle-size oracle)"
        href="/docs/widget"
      />
    </ul>
  </section>

  <section class="narrative" aria-labelledby="how-it-works-heading">
    <h2 id="how-it-works-heading">How it works</h2>

    <p>
      You embed a 17&nbsp;KB JavaScript widget on your site. A user submits a
      bug, a feature idea, or a question. Your team triages it in the admin
      console &mdash; status flows from submitted to triaged to in&nbsp;progress
      to resolved or declined, with a single typed reply attached at each step.
    </p>

    <p>
      Feature requests can be promoted to a public roadmap that voters
      upvote. The promoted text is the feedback body verbatim, with no
      submitter attribution attached &mdash; that&apos;s a load-bearing
      invariant, not a setting. When status changes, the original submitter
      gets a single email; no marketing blasts, no re-engagement campaigns,
      no list rentals, no analytics pixels.
    </p>

    <p>
      The widget is anonymous-by-default. If your app already signs a JWT
      for the user, feedbackmonk verifies the claim and attaches it to the
      submission &mdash; that JWT is the only identity feedbackmonk ever
      holds. No callbacks to your auth provider, no long-lived bearer
      tokens, no cookies set on the user&apos;s root domain.
    </p>

    <p>
      You can run it as SaaS on our infrastructure, or self-host the
      AGPL-licensed source via <code>docker compose up</code>. The Self-host
      tier is the same binary, the same migrations, the same admin UI &mdash;
      no carve-outs. See <a href="/docs/self-host">/docs/self-host</a> for
      the operator runbook.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section class="cta-section" aria-labelledby="final-cta-heading">
    <h2 id="final-cta-heading">Get started</h2>
    <p>
      Pick a tier on <a href="/pricing">/pricing</a>, or read the
      <a href="/docs/self-host">self-host runbook</a> to run feedbackmonk
      on your own infrastructure today.
    </p>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>

<style>
  .hero {
    padding-block: 2.5rem 1.5rem;
  }
  .eyebrow {
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
    font-size: 0.8125rem;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    letter-spacing: 0.08em;
    color: var(--brand-muted);
    margin: 0 0 1rem;
  }
  .hero-cta {
    display: flex;
    flex-wrap: wrap;
    gap: 0.75rem;
    margin-top: 1.5rem;
  }
  .btn-primary, .btn-secondary {
    display: inline-block;
    padding: 0.75rem 1.25rem;
    border-radius: var(--brand-radius);
    text-decoration: none;
    font-weight: 600;
  }
  .btn-primary {
    background: var(--brand-sage-deep);
    color: var(--brand-cream);
  }
  .btn-primary:hover,
  .btn-primary:focus-visible {
    background: var(--brand-ink);
    color: var(--brand-cream);
  }
  .btn-secondary {
    color: var(--brand-ink);
    border: 1px solid var(--brand-rule);
    background: var(--brand-cream);
  }
  .btn-secondary:hover,
  .btn-secondary:focus-visible {
    border-color: var(--brand-ink);
    color: var(--brand-ink);
    text-decoration: none;
  }

  .trust-section {
    margin: 2.5rem 0;
    padding: 1.5rem;
    background: var(--brand-cream);
    border: 1px solid var(--brand-rule);
    border-radius: var(--brand-radius);
  }
  .trust-heading {
    font-size: 1.125rem;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    letter-spacing: 0.06em;
    color: var(--brand-muted);
    margin-bottom: 1rem;
  }
  .trust-list {
    list-style: none;
    margin: 0;
    padding: 0;
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fit, minmax(14rem, 1fr));
    gap: 1rem;
  }

  .narrative {
    margin-block: 2.5rem;
  }
  .narrative h2 {
    margin-bottom: 0.75rem;
  }

  .cta-section {
    margin-block: 2.5rem;
    padding: 1.25rem 1.5rem;
    background: var(--brand-rule);
    border-radius: var(--brand-radius);
  }
  .cta-section h2 {
    font-size: 1.25rem;
  }
  .cta-section p {
    margin: 0;
  }
</style>
